 Lessons Learned

Vanilla JS is powerful — You don't need a framework for everything. This portfolio has animations, a terminal emulator, virtual file system, and Easter eggs — all in pure JavaScript.

Easter eggs make it memorable — The BSOD and The Final Boss Easter eggs are what people remember and share. Don't underestimate the power of fun.

CSS animations are underrated — The glitch effect, scan line, and neon pulse are all pure CSS. No JavaScript needed.

Documentation matters — Having README, CHANGELOG, CONTRIBUTING, CODE_OF_CONDUCT, SECURITY, and ROADMAP files makes the project look professional and trustworthy.

Build in public — Sharing my progress on dev.to, LinkedIn, and other platforms has helped me grow from 0 to 2,000+ followers.



